The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

THE FILM

 (Nandan, 2 pm, 4 pm, 6 pm) In search of her roots, Amu, a young girl brought 

 up in the US, returns to India and digs up a past that everyone 

 wants to forget. With Konkona Sen Sharma and Brinda Karat 

 , director Shonali Bose has captured a telling account of 

 the Delhi riots in her first feature film. 

THE DISPLAY

 (Max Mueller Bhavan, 3 pm to 8 pm, till January 28) Check out the 12 original 

 etchings and two lithographs lent by Gunter Grass. The display, 

 featuring works related to his earlier visit to Calcutta, 

 coincides with the author?s forthcoming trip, later this 

 month. 

THE SOIREE

 (Nazrul 

 Mancha, January 22) Presented by Desh, the music conference 

 starts with an open-for-all bhajan recital by Pandit 

 Jasraj , Haimanti Shukla and Upendra Bhatt. 




